  "body": "As a user, I want to see a list of (for example) pods and their imageIDs.\n\nThere are some hacks.\n\nI think I could use jq to get one columns:  `kubectl get pods -ojson | jq .items[].status.containerStatuses[].imageID`\n\nI think I could learn jsonpath: kubectl get pods -o jsonpath='{.items[*].status.containerStatuses[].imageID}'\n\nBut tying this back to a particular pod is hard.\n\nI would really like to do something more like:  `kubectl get pods --columns name, imageID`\n",
